<p>Climb through Okunikko's old-growth larch and beech forest to reach the pristine volcanic lake of Kirikomi, perched more than 1,400 meters above sea level. The AllTrails description notes a steady ascent on rooty singletrack before opening to crystal-clear alpine waters ringed by rugged lava domes.</p>

<p>The trail offers quiet picnic spots, shoreline reflections, and glimpses of seasonal alpine blooms. A peaceful descent passes bubbling streams and wetlands as the path returns to the trailhead near Kotoku Onsen, making this a rewarding half-day adventure for hikers seeking solitude.</p>

